{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1731955424,"nonce":"q262vnhanSD3GPMS+SUTvQtz4XY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6fHTLQ","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6571","origin":"github"},"title":"Bug: snpEff 5.2+galaxy0 will not execute with a snpEff_build_gb 5.2+galaxy0 database","message":"toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/snpeff/snpEff/5.2+galaxy0\ntoolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/snpeff/snpEff_build_gb/5.2+galaxy0\n\nRecent changes to turning off the db check seems to have problems. The warning box in blue goes away then pops back up and prevents the tool from submitting. Any server, several different test and real data runs. Has anyone been able to get this to work after the late Oct updates?\n\nWorkaround for end users:\n1. Create your snpeffdb with SnpEff build 4.3+T.galaxy6 first\n2. Then use SnpEff eff 4.3+T.galaxy2\n3. Note that you might need to submit the job a few times to get it to go through\n\nReported at https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/snpeff-database-compatibility/13923/5\n\n\nOne of the test histories: https://usegalaxy.eu/u/jenj/h/test-snpeff-build\n\nScreenshots: notice how the message will repeat and populate again if you click on the submit button a few times with v 5.2. Doing the repeat submission will allow a 4.3 job to eventually submit and run. \n\n![Screen Shot 2024-11-18 at 10 28 39 AM](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d46cf7d-925b-49fc-b65f-b763f4a26bec)\n\n\n![Screen Shot 2024-11-18 at 10 39 21 AM](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c05e8c4a-7f3f-42dd-90c5-a8d30f33f814)","files":null}]}